\title{the “Day unit” of fibered categories}
\author{jonmsterling}
\date{2023-09-20}
\taxon{definition}

\import{base-macros}
\let\B{#{B}}
\let\One{#{\mathbf{1}}}

\p{Let \prn{\B,\otimes,I,\alpha,\lambda,\rho} be a monoidal category. We may define a “Day unit” for [fibered categories](frct-0002) over \B to be given by the discrete fibration #{\Sl{\B}{I}\to \B}, which corresponds under the Grothendieck construction to the presheaf represented by #{I}.}
